      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">What Financiers Actually Evaluate</h3>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-4">5-Factor Approval Model:</h4>
        <ol class="space-y-4">
          <li>
            <strong>1. Current Income Stability (40% weight)</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Do you have consistent logistics income? Bank statements showing RM 10,000-20,000/month deposits matter more than credit score.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>2. Repayment Capacity (30% weight)</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Monthly income should be 1.5-2× monthly loan payment. Example: RM 3,000/month payment requires RM 4,500-6,000 income.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>3. Business Viability (15% weight)</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Do you have delivery contracts? Growing e-commerce/Port Klang demand? Clear business model? Proves loan is for income-generating asset.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>4. Credit History (10% weight)</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">CCRIS/CTOS records reviewed but not disqualifying. Financiers look at: reason for past defaults, time since last default, current repayment behavior.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>5. Collateral & Down Payment (5% weight)</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Lorry serves as collateral. Higher down payment (20-30%) compensates for weaker credit profiles.</p>
          </li>
