      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Key JPJ Requirements for Commercial Lorries</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>PUSPAKOM Inspection:</strong> Every 6 months for commercial vehicles. Cost: RM 55-75 per inspection. Budget RM 120-150/year per lorry.</li>
        <li><strong>Road Tax Renewal:</strong> First 2 years: Max 1 year renewal. After 2 years: Max 6 months renewal (due to increased vehicle age).</li>
        <li><strong>Commercial Vehicle License:</strong> GDL (Goods Driving License) required for lorries above 3,500 kg GVW. Ensure drivers are licensed.</li>
        <li><strong>Insurance:</strong> Comprehensive commercial vehicle insurance required. Cost: 2-4% of lorry value annually. Example: RM 140,000 lorry = RM 2,800-5,600/year.</li>
        <li><strong>Weight Compliance:</strong> Overloading fines: RM 1,000-5,000. Ensure lorry tonnage matches cargo weight.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-6 my-6">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-yellow-900 mb-2">New 2024 Regulation: Brake Test Penalty</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
